From 81afd47da0e735fc894e38960e57c6417bec1397 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anuj Mittal <anujx.mittal@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jun 2016 16:58:59 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] jhi: disable MEI driver and enable KDI

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Configuration]

Requested by Jonathan Lahav since MEI driver has
been replaced by KDI for APL-I.

MEI still remains the default driver for all other
use cases so this change can't be made upstream.

Signed-off-by: Anuj Mittal <anujx.mittal@intel.com>
---
 service/linux/jhid.conf | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/service/linux/jhid.conf b/service/linux/jhid.conf
index 9c17ecc..13390e6 100644
--- a/service/linux/jhid.conf
+++ b/service/linux/jhid.conf
@@ -15,9 +15,9 @@
 #
 # Uncomment one of the following:
 #
-transport MEI
+#transport MEI
 #transport SOCKET
-#transport KERNEL
+transport KERNEL
 #
 #
 #
